# Financial Performance KPIs

Core financial metrics that measure an agency's ability to capture value, control costs, and generate profit.

## Core Metrics

| KPI | Definition | Formula | Target / Benchmark | Category |
|-----|------------|---------|-------------------|----------|
| **AGI (Agency Gross Income)** | Total revenue minus pass-through costs (media spend, subcontractors, production costs, etc.) | Total Revenue - Pass-Through Costs | — | Revenue |
| **AGI %** | Agency Gross Income as percentage of total revenue | (AGI ÷ Total Revenue) × 100 | **≥ 90%** | Revenue Quality |
| **Unburdened Compensation %** | Total payroll (before taxes/benefits) as percentage of AGI | (Total Payroll ÷ AGI) × 100 | **< 45%** | Cost Control |
| **SG&A %** | Selling, General & Administrative expenses (non-payroll overhead) as percentage of AGI | (SG&A Costs ÷ AGI) × 100 | **< 20%** | Cost Control |
| **Total Costs %** | Combined payroll and overhead as percentage of AGI | ((Payroll + SG&A) ÷ AGI) × 100 | **< 65%** | Cost Control |
| **Operating Profit %** | Remaining margin after all operating costs | ((AGI - Total Costs) ÷ AGI) × 100 | **> 35%** | Profitability |

## Rules of Thumb

### AGI Margin Structure
Healthy agencies target the following cost distribution:

- **Payroll (Labor):** ≤ 45% of AGI
- **Overhead (SG&A):** ≤ 20% of AGI
- **Operating Profit:** ≥ 35% of AGI

### AGI Quality Considerations

**High-Quality AGI:**
- Comes from delivery you directly control and optimize
- Internal labor, IP, systems, strategy
- Minimal pass-through dependencies

**Low-Quality AGI:**
- Heavy reliance on media spend pass-throughs
- High subcontractor/white-label costs
- One-time production passthroughs

### Pass-Through Cost Types

| Type | Examples | Impact on AGI Quality |
|------|----------|----------------------|
| **Media/Ad Spend** | Facebook, Google, TikTok ads | Lowest-value pass-through; minimal margin |
| **Subcontracted Labor** | Freelancers, white-label services | Mid-value; some markup potential |
| **Production Costs** | Print, events, shoots, equipment | Episodic; typically neutral margin |
| **Software/Platform Fees** | SaaS tools resold to clients | Can be profitable with strategic markup |

## Revenue Hierarchy

When evaluating agency financials, mature operators break down revenue into tiers:

| Metric | Description | Use Case |
|--------|-------------|----------|
| **Gross Billings (GB)** | All invoiced client revenue including pass-throughs | Topline optics; not useful for profit analysis |
| **Adjusted Gross Income (AGI)** | GB minus true pass-throughs | Baseline for measuring profitability |
| **Net AGI** (aka "Net Revenue") | AGI minus contractor/white-label costs | Reveals core economic engine of internal teams |

## Interpretation Notes

- **Upward AGI%** indicates improved margin control and value capture
- **Rising Compensation%** can signal team expansion or declining efficiency
- **Increasing SG&A%** suggests overhead bloat or infrastructure investment
- **Stable ratios** at optimized ranges indicate operational maturity
- **Consistency matters** — sustained stability often signals systemic maturity and predictability

